.name
CapShift
.author
Alessandro Sala 
.description
Simple commodity which turns the shift key into a 'capslocktoggle' key: if
capslock is off, the shift key + an alphabetic key produces an uppercase
character, as usual; if capslock is on, the shift key + an alphabetic key
produces a lowercase character.  Can also disable capslock when a function
key or a qualifier is pressed.  
.described-by
Automatically generated from Contents file by c2pi program.
.short
CapShift
